{
  "stem": "17426.6",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Janina, ?] from several of those satellite camps of Buna for Auschwitz III.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when we arrived in-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Gutenbrunn-- when we arrived in-- in Buchenwald, we were 46,000 or 48,000. 16,000 lost their life on this death march.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] About five days of walking and about eight days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were brought to Gleiwitz this time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Gleiwitz was Germany.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a town.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there we were loaded on-- on open.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This time.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When we left Furstengrube-- when we left, rather, Gutenbrunn in the summer, we were put on closed cars.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This time we were put on open cars.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was January 1945.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were driven, again, on one of these horrible, horrendous trips to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And again, people were dying in [? groves. ?] When we came to Buchenwald, there wasn't room for us in Buchenwald, because a lot of the other camps were also being liquidated and brought west.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were lying just in the field for two or three days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't have an organized meal time, where we would get bread and soup or coffee.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "From time to time, we get something from time to time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "From a day or so, we didn't get anything at all.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Till they put us on the same wagons after three, four days and brought us to Harz Mountain to a camp called Dora Nordhausen.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Dora Nordhausen was a different camp altogether.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Dora Nordhausen was very unusual, not like anything that we have ever seen, because the camp was in the mountain, in the caves of the mountain.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
